\pard\f0\fs28 Herbaceous perennials, usually with tubers or stolons.Leaves simple, alternate. Flowers yellow. Involucral bracts in 2-3 rows, herbaceous. Receptacle convex, often hairy. Ligulate florets female, in 1 row; tubular florets hermaphrodite. Achenes ribbed; pappus of 1-2 rows of simple hairs or sometimes absent in ligulate florets.
