\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. D. corsicum} (Loisel.) Poiret in Lam., {\i Encycl. Méth. Bot., Suppl.}{\b  2}: 517 (1812) ({\i Aronicum corsicum} (Loisel.) DC.). Stems up to 120 cm, glandular-hairy above, more or less glabrous below. Basal leaves 9-16 × 3-7 cm, ovate, shortly petiolate; cauline leaves ovate-lanceolate to lanceolate, acute or acuminate, amplexicaul, sinuate-dentate, glabrous or sparsely pubescent.Capitula 2·5-4·5(-5) cm in diameter, 3-8 in a terminal corymb; peduncles glandular-pubescent. Involucral bracts 7-11(-15) mm, lanceolate, glandular-pubescent, shortly ciliate. All achenes with a pappus. 2n = 60.{\i  By mountain streams. • Corse.} Co.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. D. austriacum} Jacq., {\i Fl. Austr.}{\b  2}: 18 (1774) ({\i D. orphanidis} Boiss.). Stems up to 100 cm, glabrous, or hairy with long crispate hairs. Basal leaves 9-13 × 6-8 cm, ovate, obtuse, somewhat cordate, petiolate; lower cauline leaves ovate to lanceolate, panduriform, amplexicaul; upper cauline leaves ovate-lanceolate, pubescent or more or less glandular-puberulent, entire or denticulate. Capitula 3·5-6 cm in diameter, 5-12(-17) in a terminal corymb; peduncles glandular-pubescent. Involucral bracts 11-15 mm, linear-lanceolate, more or less pubescent. Achenes of marginal florets without a pappus. 2n = 60. {\i Damp or shady places. Mountains of C. & S. Europe, from C. France and the Carpathians southwards to N.W. Spain, N. Appennini and N. Greece.} Al Au Bu Cz Ga Ge Gr Hs Hu It Ju Po Rm Rs (W).
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. D. columnae} Ten., {\i Fl. Nap. }{\b 1}, {\i Prodr.}: 49 (1811) ({\i D. cordatum} auct., non Lam.). Stems 12-60 cm, glabrous or sparsely pubescent. Rhizome glabrous or sparsely pubescent. Basal leaves 3-7(-8) × 3-6·5(-7·5) cm, ovate-orbicular or cordate, long-petiolate, glabrous or pubescent, especially on the margin, crenate-dentate; cauline leaves 3-4, the lower elliptical to ovate-lanceolate, sometimes weakly panduriform, amplexicaul, the upper ovate-lanceolate, amplexicaul. Capitula solitary, (2-)2·5-5(-6) cm in diameter; peduncles glandular-pubescent. Involucral bracts 8-14(-18) mm, linear-lanceolate, c. ½ as long as ligules, densely glandular-pubescent. Achenes of marginal florets without a pappus. {\i Shady mountain rocks. E. Alps, Appennini, mountains of Romania and Balkan peninsula.} Al Au Bu Ge Gr It Ju Rm Rs (W).
\par

\par

